{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d93433d0-9ee4-40b4-a7fe-1411e6901b4d","content":"The `dump-collect` skill I have is specifically for **collecting** crash dumps, not analyzing them. But I can point you in the right direction for analysis:\n\n**Tools for analyzing .dmp files:**\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze <file.dmp>`** — cross-platform, .NET-focused\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n   dotnet-dump analyze crash.dmp\n   ```\n   Useful commands inside: `clrstack`, `pe` (print exception), `dumpheap`, `threads`\n\n2. **`lldb`** (Linux/macOS) — with SOS plugin for managed debugging\n\n3. **WinDbg** (Windows) — with SOS extension (`!analyze -v`, `!clrstack`)\n\n**Quick triage steps with `dotnet-dump analyze`:**\n```\n> threads          # list all threads\n> setthread <id>   # switch to faulting thread\n> pe               # print last exception\n> clrstack         # managed call stack\n> clrstack -all    # all thread stacks\n```\n\nWant me to help you run `dotnet-dump analyze` on your dump file if it's accessible in this environment?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"329b542e-7728-4e46-8ac3-ac209ce05c8d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description specifically says:\n\n- USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps, capturing dumps, setting up dump collection\n- DO NOT USE FOR: **analyzing or debugging dumps**, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is NOT appropriate here since the user wants to analyze an existing dump, not collect one.\n\nLet me help them directly with guidance on analyzing the dump.","outputTokens":421},"id":"fe2e3919-7c35-4692-8a70-9fdb9b9b9ec9","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:05:02.989Z","parentId":"c014f236-61e6-4ab1-9045-9932e9815791"}
